<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-06-03T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-06-03T18:00:00-05:00" n="609" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d609">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860c.24/51 supp.: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Poland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Pearson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-06-03T19:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 3,
                                        1925—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>46. Department’s telegram No. 1, dated January 5, 4 p.m. Discreetly
                            ascertain whether contract for the purchase of arms has been concluded
                            by the Government of Poland.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
